These fourteen (14) individual elements of Facility's prevention program work together to prevent accidental chemical releases along with mitigating their impacts. The Pasco Terminal's employees are committed to the standards required by these management programs. In addition to the above elements, the facility also has specific prevention measures that are
employed as part of its operating procedures and engineering/administrative controls to help quickly detect, contain/control, and reduce the consequences of a release. These are briefly summarized as follows:

General Risk Reduction and Safety Measures

-Engineering and construction in accordance with recognized industry and corporate standards (ex. NFPA 58); 
-Equipment properly designed with protection from overpressure (pressure safety relief valves, etc.); 
-Updated technical drawings, Piping & Instrumentation Diagrams and Process/Block Flow Diagrams;
-Operating systems monitored and controlled by trained personnel along with 24/7 remote monitoring; 
-Redundant automated control systems and system UPS; 
-Automatic and manual shutdown devices for critical systems; 
-Scheduled inspection and testing of instruments, butane-containing components, and safety devices; 
-Secured facility access; 
-Regular safety meetings and awareness programs; 
-Routinely scheduled safety inspections and audits; and 
-Frequent unit surveillance by operators. 

